.IX Title "SFF_TO_CA 1"
.TH SFF_TO_CA 1 "2015-07-29" "perl v5.8.8" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.SH "NAME"
sff_to_CA.pl \- run sffToCA from the wgs\-assembler software package. This script acts as a wrapper to ensure input is handled correctly in the Ergatis framework.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\s-1USAGE:\s0 sff_to_CA.pl
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
\&\fB\-\-sff_file, \-s\fR 
    A single sff file input.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-sff_file_list, \-sl\fR
    A list of sff files to act as input to a single \s-1CA\s0 assembly run.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-sff_to_CA_exe, \-exe\fR
    Path to the sffToCA executable.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-library, \-lib\fR
    The \s-1UID\s0 of the library these reads are added to.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-clear, \-c\fR
    Can be one of four options:
        * none 
        * soft
        * hard
        * chop
.PP
\&\fB\-\-linker, \-lk\fR
    Search for linker, created mated reads.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-trim, \-t\fR
    Trim back a specific amount of bases before the first N.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-insert_size, \-is\fR
    Mates are on average i +\- d bp apart.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-output, \-o\fR
    Output path where fragment files will be placed.
.PP
\&\fB\-\-log, \-l\fR
    Log file
.PP
\&\fB\-\-debug\fR
    Debug level
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Wrapper for the sffToCA executable. Ensures that input and parameters are correctly formatted for use in the Ergatis framework.
.SH "INPUT"
.IX Header "INPUT"
Either a single or list of \s-1SFF\s0 files that will comprise a single assembly.
.SH "OUTPUT"
.IX Header "OUTPUT"
Fragment files that are ready to be supplied to the celera-assembler
